    Create a function to display itinerary and duration:
    a. Retrieve itinerary and duration information from the database.
        Initialize a variable "itinerary" and retrieve itinerary information from the database
        Initialize a variable "duration" and retrieve duration information from the database
        b. Display the information to the customer in a user-friendly format.
        Create a template for displaying itinerary and duration
        Use the retrieved values to fill the template
        Display the filled template on the screen
        c. Provide an option to print or save the information for future reference.
        Add a print button to the page
        Add a save button to the page
        When the user clicks on the print button, print the itinerary and duration on the page
        When the user clicks on the save button, save the itinerary and duration to the local storage
        d. If there is no itinerary or duration information, display a message indicating that the information is not available.
        Check if the retrieved itinerary and duration values are null
        If either value is null, display a message indicating that the information is not available

    Create a user interface to access the function:
    a. Add a button or link on the customer's account page to access the function.
        Add a link or button to the customer's account page with the text "View Itinerary"
        Style the link or button to make it visible and easy to use
        b. Make the button or link clearly visible and easy to use.
        Use a contrasting color for the link or button to make it visible
        Add a tooltip or text next to the link or button to describe the function
        c. Add a tooltip or explanation to describe the function.
        Add a tooltip or text next to the link or button to describe the function

    Test the function:
    a. Ensure that the function works as expected.
        Test the function with different itinerary and duration values
        Test the function with different browsers and devices
        Ensure that the print and save buttons work as expected
        b. Get feedback from users to improve the function if necessary.
        Ask customers to provide feedback on the function
        Analyze the feedback to identify areas of improvement
        Implement the improvements based on the feedback provided.